<br>
Most people equate the word 'beat' with 'abuse'.<br>
<br>
I think that until you've been a severely abused child that you really can't know how it feels to see someone say that someone's parents should beat them.<br>
<br>
I can tell you how it feels.<br>
<br>
It feels horrible and shocking that anyone might even hint around about condoning that kind of behavior.<br>
<br>
How would you like to live in fear of going home each day from school, worried that you're going to get beat within an inch of your life for whatever it is you did this time? That no matter what you do, you cannot appease the person who is beating you? That they do not listen to you. That they do not hear you when you say: please don't hit me like that.<br>
<br>
Lets not forget the words that often accompany shit like this. The comments about how worthless you are. How you're never up to any good. That this hurts them more than it hurts you. That they wished you had never been born?<br>
<br>
To you, those of you, any of you, who condone beating, I tell you ever so politely -- bugger off.<br>
<br>
I see nothing wrong with discipline, and maybe even a spanking done with the hand and a swat on the rump a few times, but better not to do it at all if you can help it. Too many people cannot control their anger and let it get out of hand, and the next thing you know, your step father is kicking you down the hallway to your room because you didn't clean it.<br>
