<br>
Do you think its wrong to give a kid a tap on the bottom if they wont respond to being told no, or are acting up severely?  I think something like that is very situational, and different children need to be raised in different ways.<br>
<br>
Certainly, I think any reasonable person can agree that its wrong to smack your kids around... but generations upon generations were brought up spanked, and it hardly brought about the end of the world.<br>
<br>
I myself am not a parent, but if/when I do have children, I would absolutely use a spanking as a last deterrent.  I think though, that children need to be taught a very clear lesson about responsibility for their actions... and need to learn that if you don't do the adult and mature thing (listen when told to stop, continue to do something after a &quot;softer&quot; punishment like time out or loss of privileges,) then you suffer immediate and shocking circumstances.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if I'm wording this right, as its a hard stance to take, but I don't feel that spanking is synonymous with beating, nor would I say spanking your child immediately marks you as a poor parent.<br>
