I do believe you missed the line where I said there is a difference between discipline (ie, the occasional spanking) and abuse (which many of you are eluding to).  <br>
<br>
What I object to is the &quot;Oh, I can't EVER smack my child on the bottom, that's abuse.&quot;  No, it's not.  And I guarentee if more children these days had occasionally had their britches warmed by mom or dad, they wouldn't be nearly the handful they are.  <br>
<br>
Case in point:  I used to have a neighbor.  His mom was very much the PC, I'll just take away his toys, his nintendo, his playtime, and he'll learn.  Yeah, he learned.  To punch her in the eye, giving her a nice raccoon look for about a week.  He got his lovely toys back too.  Now, if she'd taken him over her knee before he was big enough to beat on her, he might have respected her just a bit more.  <br>
I know he certainly respected my mother, after she caught him in our barn trying to start a nice lil fire.  She had him up against a fence faster than he could scream for grandpa, and all the time he was telling her he'd tell his grandpa and she'd be sorry, she just nodded.  When he was done she said &quot;Well, your grandpa isn't here right now, and I am.  And you may go and tell him, and go and tell the cops, but just remember son, I'll get a piece of you first.&quot;  She let him go, without a scratch, but he never again set foot on our property without being invited.  In fact, he was sweet as punch to me for the rest of the time I lived there as well.  Was quite the change from the boy who tried to choke me to death in the middle of a wheat field.  *shrugs*<br>
<br>
Some kids need that physical discipline.  Or they keep pushing the line, and become complete and total horrors.  I'm not saying all kids do, or that abuse of any sort is to be tolerated.  But the occasional spanking is NOT going to harm a child psychologically, or physically.  I will stand by my assertion that it will do them more good in the end.  <br>
<br>
Again, so no one misses my point.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>There is a difference between DISCIPLINE and ABUSE.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  One can be a good thing, the other is never good.  I know, I've been subject to both.  There is a difference, and it's in the parent.  Some parents wish only to show a strong consequence to their child, and often do not need to do so again.  Others...well, they should never have been allowed to breed in the first place.  However, the political correctness revolving around parenting today seriously hinders the one, while not even putting a stop to the other.  It makes me sad to see it.<br>
<br>
