<br>
To those that say you should never spank your children or use physical punishment, I would say history and experience say you are most definately wrong.<br>
<br>
To those who claim that all forms of physical correction are abuse, it is unfortunate if you were abused but using extreme examples as empirical proof isnt very accutrate or productive.<br>
<br>
I have seen parents that raised there children with displine and ones that used the softer none physical approach. From what I have seen the ones raised with disipline tend to have better lives as adults.<br>
<br>
My wife and I raised our children with discipline and spankings when required. Our children did not grow up to hate us. Instead now that they are adults we have mutual respect and we are the closest of friends.<br>
<br>
When my sons decided they wanted to return to colledge they came back home. They could have afforded to live somewhere else or in dorms but they felt comfortable in our house and knew they were welcome.<br>
<br>
I can't say what is best for everyone but I can say what I have seen that works and what doesn't. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=406740" target="&quot;web&quot;">&lt;<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Baron Siffo Corpsestalker</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
